FBIS4-37571 "drnes120_j_94018" FBIS-NES-94-120 Daily Report 19 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Deputy Prime Minister, Italian Ambassador Discuss Ties Deputy Prime Minister, Italian Ambassador Discuss Ties JN1906135094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1200 GMT 19 Jun 94 JN1906135094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Deputy Prime Minister Brother 'Abd-al-Qadir Ba Jammal today received Italian Ambassador (Peter Mordoni). They discussed ties between the two friendly countries and prospects for expanding and developing them. They also reviewed developments in the Yemeni arena and exchanged views on several issues of mutual concern. The brother deputy prime minister voiced appreciation for the principled positions adopted by the Italian Government toward the current conditions in our country and its support for the Republic of Yemen on the basis of the strong historical ties between the Yemeni and Italian peoples. The meeting was attended by (Giovani Etelling), the Italian charge d'affaires in Sanaa.
